The MSI MEG X670E ACE Motherboard offers 2x PCIe Gen 5 x16 slots and 4x M.2 slots. It comes with a generous amount of cache, including a 1.5MB L1 cache, 12MB L2 cache, and an impressive 128MB L3 cache. The default thermal design power (TDP) is 280W, ensuring efficient operation under heavy workloads. The processor is built using TSMC's 7nm FinFET process and supports overclocking for enthusiasts seeking even higher performance. It utilizes the sWRX8 CPU socket and is compatible with a single-socket configuration. The AMD Ryzen Threadripper PRO 5965WX offers excellent connectivity with PCIe 4.0 support and supports DDR4 memory with up to 3200MHz speed. It does not have integrated graphics and requires a discrete graphics card for visual output.
